HEADWORD: Decidua
<hw>De*cid"u*a</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
L. <ets>deciduus</ets>. See <er>Deciduous</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The inner layer of the wall of the uterus, which
envelops the embryo, forms a part of the placenta, and is discharged
with it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

